Environment: schema-only npm package (`@meavo/db`) — the canonical Prisma 6 schema for the ONE shared Neon Postgres database used by all MEAVO apps. This is the only repo allowed to alter the database. There is no app code here.

## Stack

- Prisma 6 schema (`prisma/schema.prisma`) → PostgreSQL (Neon), ~125 models / ~54 enums
- Consumed by app repos as a git dependency pinned to a tag (`#v0.x.y`); they run `prisma generate` only
- Idempotent SQL scripts in `scripts/` for targeted/destructive migrations via `prisma db execute`
- No framework, tests, lint, or build — safety net is `npm run validate` + `npm run diff`

## Do NOT

- Run `prisma migrate dev` or introduce a migrations directory — this repo uses `db push` + idempotent `scripts/*.sql`.
- Run `db:push` without first reading `npm run diff` output — a push after removing/renaming models drops other apps' live tables.
- Rename/delete another app's models, fields, or enums without checking every consumer (ownership table in `README.md`).
- Duplicate identity tables — foreign-key to the shared gateway `User` / `Team` models.
- Add app code, seeds, or generated client output — schema + SQL scripts only.
- Point consumer apps at untagged commits — tag `v0.x.y` first.
- Commit `.env` or secret values.

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Canonical schema (organized by owning app) | `prisma/schema.prisma` |
| Targeted / destructive SQL migrations | `scripts/*.sql` |
| Table-ownership matrix | `README.md` |
| Migration safety + domain docs | `docs/data-model.md`, `docs/architecture.md` |

## Data flow

```
edit prisma/schema.prisma → npm run validate → npm run diff (review SQL!)
  → npm run db:push  (or prisma db execute --file scripts/x.sql for destructive steps)
  → commit + bump package.json version + git tag v0.x.y + push --tags
  → bump @meavo/db git ref in each affected app → npm install + prisma generate → redeploy
```

Every schema change must end with a tagged release and a dependency bump in the affected apps — an applied-but-untagged schema leaves apps generating stale clients.

